ANNOTATION OF NATURAL SCIENCE SPREADSHEETS



DESCRIPTION
Automatic Annotation of Natural Science Spreadsheets as performed in the paper "Combining Information on Structure and Content to Automatically
Annotate Natural Science Spreadsheets"  by Martine de Vos, Jan Wielemaker, Hajo Rijgersberg, Guus Schreiber,Bob Wielinga,Jan Top in International
Journal of Human Computer Studies 2016


SOURCE CODE (prolog)
- initialBlocks.pl
- annotateBlocks.pl
- annotateTerms.pl
- evaluateBlocks.pl
- evaluateTerms.pl


INPUT DATA
- open document spreadsheets to annotate; we used LiteratureSpreadsheets.ods 
 (NB: the color markup of the blocks is for our own convenience and not recognized by the automatic annotation)
- list of manually annotated spreadsheet terms
- list of manually annotated spreadsheet blocks
 Two RDF repositories on the server: the OM vocabulary http://www.wurvoc.org/vocabularies/om-1.8/ 
  and the Valerie vocabulary  http://www.foodvoc.org/page/Valerie


OTHER PREREQUISITES
- Installation of SWI Prolog
- A semantic web server; we used ClioPatria http://cliopatria.swi-prolog.org/home
- plsheet library by Jan Wielemaker


DEPLOYMENT
Load a file:
init_file("PathToSpreadsheet").

Annotate spreadsheet:
annotate_tables.

Evaluate annotation of terms:
aggregate_all(count,Term-Concept,term_map_agree(Term,Concept,sheet_labels),Total).


AUTHORS
Jan Wielemaker
Martine de Vos
